title: Anishinaabe (North American people)
vocabulary: Preferred subject headings for North American Indigenous peoples
definition: Preferred topical term to describe resources about the Anishinaabe people of North America.
usage: Use this term to supplement or replace close matches in LCSH or other external vocabularies. When assigning this term, also assign the indicated narrower terms if appropriate.
history: This term is acceptable for describing the Odawa, per an email from a representative of the Little River Band of Ottawa Indians, 2021-07-06. This term also is acceptable for describing the Odawa, Ojibwe, and Bodwéwadmik peoples more broadly, per an email from a representative of the Grand Traverse Band of Ottawa and Chippewa Indians, 2021-09-17.
alternative_form: Algic; Anishinabe; Bawichtigoutek; Bungee; Bungi; Chipouais; Chippewa; Lac Courte Oreilles; Ochepwa; Odjibway; Ojibwa; Ojibwe; Ottawa; Outaouak; People of the Three Fires; Tawa
narrower_term: Bodwéwadmik (North American people);Odawa (North American people);Ojibwe (North American people)
communities: Grand Traverse Band of Ottawa and Chippewa Indians;Citizen Potawatomi Nation;Prairie Band Potawatomi Nation;Ottawa Tribe of Oklahoma;Little Traverse Bay Bands of Odawa Indians;Little River Band of Ottawa Indians

title: Bodwéwadmik (North American people)

history: This term is acceptable per emails from representatives of the Prairie Band Potawatomi Nation, 2021-07-12, and the Citizen Potawatomi Nation, 2021-09-20.
alternative_form: Neshnabek; People of the Place of Fire; Potawatomi; Pottawatamie; Pottowatomie; Prairie People; Shkotani
communities: Citizen Potawatomi Nation;Prairie Band Potawatomi Nation

title: Dakota (North American people)
vocabulary: Preferred subject headings for North American Indigenous peoples
definition: Preferred topical term to describe resources about the Dakota people of North America.
usage: Use this term to supplement or replace close matches in LCSH or other external vocabularies.
